  "couplingIntensity": "None",
  "created": "2026-03-16",
  "description": "Sculpting the instability of memory. memoryDrift holds at 0.35 — the past version of the sound gently detuned, a barely perceptible warble beneath the main signal. Mod wheel increases drift to 0.88: the memory layer becomes increasingly detuned and unstable, the historical version of each note drifting away from pitch, the two layers diverging into a beating, wavering dissonance. At maximum drift the past sounds like a waterlogged piano in a flooding room. Aftertouch reanchors — pulls drift back down sharply, the memory version snapping back into tune, the instability resolved. Release and it begins drifting again. Velocity determines initial grainSize — soft strikes begin with large grains, long reconstruction; hard strikes begin with tight grains, the memory more precise before the drift takes it.",
